'''Charles Hastings Collette''' (1816–1901)<ref>{{Citation | title = Books | accessdate = 23 Dec 2013 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=NLQ7mgEACAAJ | publisher = Google}}.</ref> was a British 19th-century [[solicitor]] and writer of [[Protestant]] popular controversialist [[apologetics]].<ref>{{Citation | url = https://encrypted.google.com/search?sa=X&tbm=bks&tbm=bks&q=inauthor:%22Charles+Hastings+Collette | title = Books | publisher = Google | type = search results | contribution = Charles Hastings Collette}}.</ref> He was the father of actor [[Charles Henry Collette]] and the organizer of the [[Joseph Mendham]] library. As a volunteer in the First Middlesex Artillery, he compiled a handbook for drill instruction.<ref>Charles Hastings Collette, ''The Handy Book of Company Drill and Practical Instructor, Etc'', Houlston & Wright, 1862, [https://books.google.com/books?id=rr9XAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA29&lpg=PA29&dq=wheeling+pivot&source=bl&ots=C9rypPgTVL&sig=0PYjkhYz43tKmnIaaBswgkj6vjE&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiC5KHCpYbUAhVCbSYKHYGJCdYQ6AEILzAB#v=onepage&q=wheeling%20pivot&f=false pp. 27–33].</ref>
His ''[[Novelties of Romanism]]'',{{Sfn | Collette | 1863}} developed from a sermon,{{Sfn | Collette | 1842}} was translated into Spanish and, from Spanish, into Portuguese (under the translated name of '''''Carlos'' Hastings Collette''') and remains in print to this day.{{Sfn | Collette | 2001}}
