[[File:Marbas Seal.jpg|thumb|The [[Sigil (magic)|Sigil]] of Marbas. ]]
In [[demonology]], '''Marbas''' or '''Barbas''' is a [[demon]] described in the [[Ars Goetia]].  He is described as the Great President of [[Hell]] governing thirty-six legions of demons. He answers truly on hidden or secret things, causes and heals diseases, teaches medical arts, and changes men into other shapes. He is depicted as a great lion that, under the conjurer's request, changes shape into a man.

The name Barbas also comes from the [[Latin]] "barba", beard, [[hellebore]] (a plant used in [[witchcraft]], especially to invoke demons), and also a male name. {{Citation needed|date=February 2007}}

== In popular culture ==
* Marbas is the name of a demon in [[The Priests (film)|''The Priests'']].
* Bob Barbas is the name of a demon in [[DmC: Devil May Cry|''DmC Devil May Cry'']].
* Barbas is the name of the dog which accompanies the daedric prince Clavicus Vile in ''[[The Elder Scrolls]]'' series.

