{{LDSpolygamy}}
'''Polygamy czar''' is an informal title given to the "Investigator of Crimes within Closed Societies" for the [[State attorney general|Utah Attorney General's]] Office. The position was established by the [[Utah State Legislature]] in 2000.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/nation/2001-05-13-polygamist.htm |title= Polygamist goes on trial in Utah |first= Patrick |last= O'Driscoll |date= June 19, 2001 |newspaper= [[USA Today]] |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20141022020521/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/nation/2001-05-13-polygamist.htm |archive-date= 2014-10-22 |dead-url= no }}</ref> The office is responsible for investigating [[tax evasion]], [[welfare fraud]], [[child abuse]], [[sex abuse]], [[domestic violence]] and other crimes committed within [[Fundamentalist Mormon]] communities that practice [[plural marriage]].

A fictionalized czar was introduced in the [[HBO]] series ''[[Big Love]]'' in the episode "Affair."

